ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend this course. It should be a staple seminar for anyone in the program.
Highly recommended, as long as you don't mind a heavy workload. Good for both historians and theorists.
The course is an introduction to the major scholarly debates surrounding the study of late Beethoven. I would recommend the course to another student.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I found the meta-critical aspect of the course the most valuable. In general, I think the class raised many questions that are important for budding humanist scholars to consider.
